text: Kucherbayevo () is a rural locality (a village) in Ryazanovsky Selsoviet, Sterlitamaksky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 332 as of 2010. There are 3 streets. == Geography == It is located 19 km from Sterlitamak, 7 km from Ryazanovka. == References == Category:Rural localities in Sterlitamaksky District
title: Kucherbayevo
